<div class="hero"><div class="hero-inner">
<div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Comparison</div>
<h1 class="hero-h">ChatGPT Plus vs <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">ChatGPT Team.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">ChatGPT Plus and Team look similar but solve different problems. Plus is individual productivity. Team is collaborative + admin. Here is the practical comparison and when to upgrade.</p>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Where Plus is enough</span><h2 class="h2">Individual use</h2>
    <p class="body"><strong>You are 1-3 people total.</strong> Below 3 active users, Team's collaboration features are wasted overhead.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>You do not share workflows.</strong> Custom GPTs you build are personal — no value in sharing.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>You do not need admin controls.</strong> Billing and user management overhead does not exist.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Combined cost lower.</strong> 3 Plus seats = $60/mo. 3 Team seats = $90/mo + minimum 5-seat requirement makes Team $150/mo.</p>
    </div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Where Team becomes necessary</span><h2 class="h2">Collaboration</h2>
    <p class="body"><strong>You have 5+ active users.</strong> Team's shared workspaces start producing value.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>You want shared GPTs.</strong> A team-built GPT with company knowledge loaded benefits everyone.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>You need admin controls.</strong> Centralized billing, user provisioning, access management.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>You have data sensitivity concerns.</strong> Team excludes your data from training by default; Plus does too but Team has clearer enterprise posture.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>You want the same baseline across the org.</strong> Standardizing on Team means everyone has the same features.</p>
    </div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">The decision rule</span><h2 class="h2">Practical guidance</h2>
    <p class="body">Under 5 people: Plus individually.</p>
    <p class="body">5+ people with shared workflows: Team.</p>
    <p class="body">50+ people or compliance requirements: Enterprise. See <a href="/claude-team-vs-claude-enterprise" style="color:#00C853;">Claude Team vs Enterprise</a> for the equivalent decision on Claude side.</p>
    </div></section>

